2014年7月15日，哈蒙德被任命为[[英国外交大臣|外交和英联邦大臣]]。报纸突出报道了他的“[[歐洲懷疑主義|欧洲怀疑主义者]]”的证据，他相信英国可以“改革”[[欧盟|欧盟]]的协议。他说如果英国和欧洲的关系不改变，他会支持[[英国脱欧|英国通过公投脱离欧盟]]。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/10969136/Philip-Hammond-I-am-serious-about-reforming-EU.html |title=Philip Hammond: I am serious about reforming EU |trans_title=哈蒙德：我认真对待改革欧盟 |work=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |accessdate=2016-12-18 |archive-date=2016-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808045627/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/10969136/Philip-Hammond-I-am-serious-about-reforming-EU.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 但[[戴维·卡梅伦|卡梅伦]]首相重启与欧盟的谈判后，哈蒙德表示自己支持留在欧盟中。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35616946 |title=EU vote: Where the cabinet and other MPs stand |trans_title=脱欧公投：内阁和国会成员站队情况 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2016-12-18 |archive-date=2018-07-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726105629/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-35616946 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

