=== 财政大臣 ===
[[File:Hammond_ready_for_2018_Autumn_Budget.jpg|thumb]]，公佈2018年度秋季財政預算]]
2016年7月13日，哈蒙德被新任首相[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]任命为财政大臣。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.sky.com/story/cabinet-hammond-chancellor-johnson-foreign-10500834 |title=Cabinet: Hammond Chancellor, Johnson Foreign |trans_title=新内阁：哈蒙德任财政大臣，约翰逊任外交大臣 |publisher=Sky News |date=14 July 2016 |accessdate=2016-12-18 |archive-date=2016-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160713190543/http://news.sky.com/story/cabinet-hammond-chancellor-johnson-foreign-10500834 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

哈蒙德曾支持[[英國去留歐盟公投|留在欧盟]]，但大局已定后他确认会支持英国退出欧盟，并说：“没有如果，没有但是，没有第二次公投，我们将离开欧盟。但同样明确的是英国人民未曾在6月23日的投票中选择更贫穷和更不安全的选项。”他会采取一切必要措施来保护经济，工作和生活水平。<ref>{{cite news|title=Philip Hammond spells out plans to tackle Brexit 'turbulence'|url=http://news.sky.com/story/philip-hammond-spells-out-plans-to-tackle-brexit-turbulence-10604388|accessdate=15 March 2017|publisher=Sky News|date=3 October 2016|archive-date=2017-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316114005/http://news.sky.com/story/philip-hammond-spells-out-plans-to-tackle-brexit-turbulence-10604388|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2016年10月，哈蒙德面临着企图“破坏英国脱欧”的指责，因为他敦促对控制移民的举措要谨慎，他被内阁同事批评“争论起来就像看什么都有风险的会计师”而不是推进脱欧计划。据了解，哈蒙德先生是上周在[[英国内阁委员会|内阁脱欧委员会]]会议中敦促谨慎的声音之一，这个会议讨论了减少移民的新工作许可证的提议，在会议上，[[英国内政大臣|内政大臣]][[安珀·路德|安珀·路德]]提出了一项脱欧后签证制度的计划，这将迫使所有来自欧盟的工人证明他们在进入英国之前获得了熟练的工作技能。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/16/philip-hammond-in-cabinet-row-over-accusations-he-is-trying-to-u/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-12-18 |archive-date=2017-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207021627/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/16/philip-hammond-in-cabinet-row-over-accusations-he-is-trying-to-u/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

根据《[[星期日泰晤士報|星期日泰晤士报]]》报道，哈蒙德的首要任务是确保英国金融业保留与欧盟[[單一市場|单一市场]]的对接。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shipmamn|first1=Tim|last2=Pancevski|first2=Bojan|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/chancellor-blamed-as-cabinet-splits-over-single-market-0wx336w3f|title=Chancellor blamed as cabinet splits over single market|work=The Sunday Times|date=28 August 2016|accessdate=17 July 2017|archive-date=2017-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114202836/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/chancellor-blamed-as-cabinet-splits-over-single-market-0wx336w3f|dead-url=no}}{{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=May|first=Joss|url=https://www.politicshome.com/news/europe/eu-policy-agenda/brexit/news/78471/theresa-may-asks-cabinet-ministers-brexit-proposals|title=Theresa May asks Cabinet ministers for Brexit proposals|work=Politics Home|date=28 August 2016|accessdate=4 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207030119/https://www.politicshome.com/news/europe/eu-policy-agenda/brexit/news/78471/theresa-may-asks-cabinet-ministers-brexit-proposals|archive-date=2017-02-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>2017年1月，他宣布，英国将离开单一市场，因为在英国脱欧公投后，继续遵守欧盟关于活动自由的所有规则在政治上是不可能的，还表示说他们会去追求一个“全面的自由贸易协定”。<ref>{{cite news|title=Hammond says Britain will leave EU single market|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-hammond-idUKKBN1511N6|accessdate=15 March 2017|publisher=Bloomberg|date=17 January 2017|archive-date=2017-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316113753/http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-hammond-idUKKBN1511N6|dead-url=no}}</ref>

哈蒙德在2017年3月的第一个预算案中增加了个体经营人士必须支付{{le|国民保险|National Insurance}}费的内容，尽管保守党在2015年大选宣言中承诺不增加国民保险。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/mar/08/philip-hammond-nics-self-employed-tory-manifesto-budget  Budget 2017: manifesto row clouds chancellor's attempt at low-key package] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/mar/08/philip-hammond-nics-self-employed-tory-manifesto-budget |date=20170408135839 }} ''[[卫报|卫报]]''</ref>一个星期后，在本党后座议员的反对下，该政策被放弃。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/mar/15/philip-hammond-ditches-national-insurance-rise-for-self-employed  Philip Hammond ditches national insurance rise for self-employed] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/mar/15/philip-hammond-ditches-national-insurance-rise-for-self-employed |date=20170408135826 }} ''The Guardian''</ref>{{le|财政研究所|Institute for Fiscal Studies}}赞成上涨国民保险费，称原来不加税的承诺不明智。“正如我们当时所说，这些承诺是愚蠢的。承诺不提高三大主要税收 - 所得税、国民保险和增值税 - 把你的手脚束缚到一个荒谬的程度。”<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-39219275 Institute for Fiscal Studies backs National Insurance increase] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-39219275 |date=20170502194702 }} ''[[BBC|BBC]]''</ref>政治记者{{le|乔治·伊顿|George Eaton}}坚持说这一承诺就是谈判的工具，因为当时保守党并不期望能完全执政。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/03/conservatives-manifesto-problems-wont-end-here|title=The Conservatives' manifesto problems won't end here|website=www.newstatesman.com|accessdate=2017-11-14|archive-date=2017-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317153941/http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/03/conservatives-manifesto-problems-wont-end-here|dead-url=no}}</ref>哈蒙德的预算延续了政府冻结福利的政策。<ref>[http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/welfare/2017/03/what-welfare-changes-did-philip-hammond-make-his-budget-2017 What welfare changes did Philip Hammond make in his Budget 2017?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/welfare/2017/03/what-welfare-changes-did-philip-hammond-make-his-budget-2017 |date=20170317002556 }} ''[[New_Statesman|New Statesman]]''</ref>

[[2017年英國大選|2017年大选]]后，哈蒙德暗示他可能在即将到来的秋季预算中放松{{le|英国政府财政紧缩计划|United Kingdom government austerity programme|紧缩政策}}。哈蒙德说：“显然我们不是聋哑人。我们收到了大选传递出的信息，我们需要找寻处理危机的对策。我明白在2008年经济危机后努力工作重建经济以使人们感到疲惫，我们必须或在现实中……我们从未承诺不加税。”<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/18/people-are-weary-of-the-slog-philip-hammond-signals-easing-of-austerity Philip Hammond hints government will ease up on austerity] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/18/people-are-weary-of-the-slog-philip-hammond-signals-easing-of-austerity |date=20170618150354 }} ''The Guardian''</ref>

哈蒙德在2017年6月的演讲中表示，英国脱欧协议首先保证是就业和繁荣，这是英国经济能够摆脱长期紧缩局面实现强劲增长的唯一途径。他呼吁在2019年底谈判时间截止前，应将全面的贸易协定、过渡协议和保持边境开放做为英国退欧计划的三个要点。他说，如果谈判能达成有利营商的协议的话，人们会“长出一口气”。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/jun/20/chancellor-philip-hammond-brexit-deal-jobs-prosperity-first |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2017-11-14 |archive-date=2017-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707050717/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/jun/20/chancellor-philip-hammond-brexit-deal-jobs-prosperity-first |dead-url=no }}</ref>

